[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      7[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Setup
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      8[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      9[0m:[38;5;10m[49m You'll need a few Python packages:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```bash
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     12[0m:[38;5;10m[49m pip install pulp numpy boto3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     14[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     15[0m:[38;5;10m[49m PuLP is a modeling library for linear and mixed-integer programming. It ships with the CBC solver (open-source, no license required), which handles assignment problems with hundreds of patients and dozens of providers in seconds. NumPy provides utility functions for working with the preference and capacity matrices.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     16[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     17[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Your environment needs AWS credentials configured (via environment variables, an instance profile, or `~/.aws/credentials`). The IAM role or user needs `s3:GetObject`, `s3:PutObject`, `dynamodb:PutItem`, and `dynamodb:GetItem`.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     18[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
